; Regression test for issue #1128: print --raw from stdin gives <no source context> (BZ#1128)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1128
; When ledger reads from stdin (-f -), the 'print --raw' command should output
; the original source text of transactions, just as it does when reading from a file.
; Instead, it silently produces no output because there is no source context to re-read.

2024/01/01 Payee
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

; Bug: print --raw from stdin produces no output instead of the original source text.
; Normal 'print' from stdin works, but '--raw' requires re-reading the source bytes.
; The current (broken) behavior is empty stdout with exit 0.
test -f - print --raw
end test
